ENBRIDGE TRANSPORTATION (IL-OK) L.L.C.
LOCAL RATE TARIFF
FROM
FLANAGAN, ILLINOIS
TO
CUSHING, OKLAHOMA
The rate listed in this tariff is subject to the Rules and Regulations published by Enbridge Transportation (IL-OK) L.L.C. FERC Tariff No.1.3.0, or successive issues thereof, for transportation within the United States. Filed in compliance with 18 C.F.R. 342.3 (Indexing). Filed in compliance with 18 C.F.R. 341.3 (Form of tariff). [C] Issued pursuant to FERC Order Reinstating Index Level issued on September 17, 2024 in Docket No. RM93-11. [C] Issued on three (3) days’ notice under authority of 18 C.F.R. 341.14. This tariff publication is conditionally accepted subject to refund pending a 30-day review period. The rate listed in this tariff is expressed in U.S. dollars. The provisions published herein will, if effective, not result in an effect on the quality of the human environment. ISSUED: May 29, 2025 EFFECTIVE: July 1, 2025
ISSUED BY: Erin Rolstad Director LP Regulatory and Mainline Commercial Strategy Enbridge Pipelines Inc. 200, Fifth Avenue Place 425 – 1st Street S.W. Calgary, AB Canada T2P 3L8 COMPILED BY: Cole Dawson LP Regulatory Enbridge Pipelines Inc. (403) 367-2027
E-mail: Enbridge-Tariffs@enbridge.com
The rate listed in this tariff is applicable on the movement of Crude Petroleum at established receiving points in the United States for the purpose of transportation on the Enbridge Transportation (IL-OK) L.L.C. System in the United States. RATES: LOSS ALLOWANCE: Enbridge Transportation (IL-OK) L.L.C. will deduct loss allowance according to the Rules and Regulations of the Carrier. ROUTING: Receipt point in the state of Illinois to delivery points in the state of Oklahoma.
TRANSPORTATION RATE FOR
ENBRIDGE TRANSPORTATION (IL-OK) L.L.C.
UNCOMMITTED RATE IN U.S. DOLLARS PER BARREL 1 CRUDE PETROLEUM DELIVERY TO: Cushing, Oklahoma From Rate Flanagan, Illinois [I] 4.6097
1 The transportation service provided under this tariff terminates at the Carrier's tanks at Cushing, Oklahoma. Any charges required to effect transfer from the Carrier's tanks will be assessed by the appropriate service provider.
SYMBOLS:
[C] – Cancel [I] – Increase
